result.execSummary:
The defendant Frank T. Erno was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Election Fraud-Illegal Voting, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 12.13(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Frank T. Erno in court with attorney Eric Sheets. Cass W Cousins appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

11:37 a.m.  Court calls case.
Atty Cousins states the appearances.

Plea questionnaire/Agreement filed.
Prosecutor states plea agreement.
Attorney for Defendant concurs with agreement stated.

Defendant enters a plea of: 
Count 1 - Guilty

Court will not accept a No Contest Plea so defendant pleads Guilty.
Court questions Defendant regarding plea.
Court informs Defendant of Constitutional Rights. Court advises Defendant of Elements State must prove for the Charge.
Court questions Attorney for Defendant.
Court finds Defendant's Plea is freely, voluntarily and intelligently made.
Attorneys stipulate that there is factual basis for the charge(s).

BY THE COURT:
Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charge(s).
Court finds the defendant guilty of Count 1.  Clerk directed to enter Judgment of Conviction this date.

Atty Cousins makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 
Atty Sheets makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 
Defendant does not wish to make a statement prior to sentencing.

BY THE COURT:
Count 1 - 
Pay $100 fine + costs to include the $250 DNA Surcharge
Pay within 60 days or set up a payment plan

Defendant Frank T. Erno in court with attorney Eric Sheets. Cass W Cousins appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State files Information.
Defendant received copy of information.
Defendant waives reading of information. 

NOT GUILTY Plea(s) entered.

Bond Continued.

Defendant Frank T. Erno in court with attorney Eric Sheets.  Atty Elizabeth Constable appeared on behalf of Cass W Cousins  for the State of Wisconsin.

3:12 p.m.  Court calls case.
Atty Constable states the appearances.

Defendant waives right to preliminary hearing. 
Court questions defendant regarding waiver of preliminary hearing. 
Court questions Attorney.
Court finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived the preliminary hearing. 
On the defendants waiver of the preliminary hearing, Court determines, based on the facts contained in the complaint, there is sufficient probable cause and binds the defendant over for trial. 

BY THE COURT:
Bond is continued
  Arraignment scheduled for June 15, 2015 at 10:00 am.

Defendant Frank T. Erno in court with attorney Eric Sheets. Cass W Cousins appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 
Attorney/Defendant received copy of criminal complaint.
Court informs defendant of charges and maximum penalties.
Attorney/Defendant waives reading of complaint.
Attorney waives time limits for preliminary hearing to be held.

State recommends a $2,000 signature bond with conditions as stated.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for May 26, 2015 at 03:00 pm.
